title: Honduras Food Inflation
description: Cost of food in Honduras increased 16.90 percent in October of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Food Inflation in Honduras averaged 5.52 percent from 2001 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 21.65 percent in July of 2008 and a record low of -5.18 percent in December of 2009. This page provides the latest reported value for - Honduras Food Inflation - plus previous releases, historical high and low, short-term forecast and long-term prediction, economic calendar, survey consensus and news.
author: Banco Central de Honduras
